review_blob: Pour from a can, dark amber color wiht off white head.  Big malty aroma.  More dark malts in the taste.  Caramel, and some roasty flavors.  Pure Maltbomb.  Decent beer.
From a can, pours a golden copper color with off white head.  Big citrusy hops in the aroma.  More of the same in the taste along with some sweet caramel malts.

From a bottle.  Pours a amber color with off white head.  Big aromas of citrusy, floral hops and some sweet malts.  More of the same in the taste.  great tasting hoppy beer.  If youre into hops a fresh one of these is what you need to drink.
From a bottle, pours a murky yellow color. Aroma of citrusy lemon,  and spicey notes.  Similiar notes in the taste with hints of lemon and wheat.

From a 22 oz bottle, pours a dark amber with large off-white head.  Big mix of citrusy, piney hops and sweet, caramel malts.  Sticky mouthfeel.  My first beer from Bear Republic and they set the bar high.
beer_name: Bear Republic Hop Rod Rye Ale

review_blob: Great beer for the summer.  Very hoppy aroma, with wheat notes.  Citrusy hops, with wheat, and lemon peel flavors.  light mouthfeel.   Great Wheat.
Great summer brew.  Notes of lemon and citrusy flavors with a hint of wheat and yeast flavors.  Very drinkable.
From bottle, pours a light copper color.  Not much going on with this beer.  Faint earthy spicey hops.   Bells has much better offering than this
Decent brew.  a nice mix of fruity, citrusy flavor.  very easy to drink, light mouthfeel.
From a bottle.  Pours a copper color.  Hoppy aroma.  sweet malt background.  slightly bitter.
From a bottle.  Pours a copper color.  Aromas of floral, piney hops.  More pine, spicey, citrus hops in the taste along with some caramel malt.  decent ipa.
From a bottle.  Pours a light golden color. Very citrusy aroma.  Sam for the taste.  Flavors of lemon and citrusy hops. Very easy to drink.
From a bottle.  Light copper color.  Aromas of citrus and floral hops.  more of the same in the taste.  slight bitter finish.  good brew.
From bottle pours a light amber color.  Aroma is floral and citrus hops.  Decent malt background.
From abomber, pours a deep copper color.  Very citrusy aroma.  Taste is more of the same citrusy, grapefruity hop flavor.  Alcohol is hidden well.  Great IIPA.
Just a great beer.  Huge citrus and grapefruit aromas and tastes.  good balance between bitter and sweet hops.  Way to easy to drink.

Pour from a 22oz bomber.  dark black with dark tan head.  huge aromas of chocolate and roasted malts.  More chocolate in the taste along with a bitter bite.  Very creamy mouthfeel.  alcohol isnt really noticable until this beer warms up.  great brew from Stone.
beer_name: Stone 20th Anniversary Encore Series: Bitter Chocolate Oatmeal Stout

review_blob: Form a 12 oz bottle, pours a copper color.  Decent hop and malt flavors.  overall average beer.
Not a bad ipa.  Classic IPA color.  Good hop presence in the aroma.  More piney hops in the taste along with some faint caramel malt.
Very watery thn beer.  little aroma or taste.  grassy notes and and faint wheat

From a 22oz bomber, pours a dark brown, nearly black color.  Coffee, dark, chocolate, piney, citrusy hoppy aroma.  The hops and dark maltyness of these 2 beers work great together.  a nice flavorful complex beer
From 22oz bomber.  Fruity, spicey hop aroma.  MOre citrusy, piney, spicey hops in the taste.  A small hint of caramel malt.  Solid IPA
beer_name: Hoppin Frog Hoppin to Heaven IPA

review_blob: From a 22oz bottle pours a hazy copper.  hoppy, piney, sweet in the aroma.  sorta soapy, bubblegun flavor in the taste with some citrusy hops.
beer_name: Sly Fox Rte. 113 India Pale Ale

review_blob: From a 22oz bottle pours a hazy copper.  big pine citrus notes in the aroma.  More piney hops in the tastes.  alcohol is well hidden.  great IIpa
A nice light drinkable pale ale.  notes of hops and malt balance well.  decent brew
beer_name: Mad River Steelhead Extra Pale Ale

review_blob: Wow a good beer in a can, awsome.  Great drinkable IPA.  solid sweet, citrusy, pine hops and malt.
Great representation of the style.  This is definetely on the fruity side of ipas.  Alot of gapefruit goodness. very good brew.

from a bottle, pours the standard copper color.  Something was off in the aroma, it sorta smelled like new shoes or fresh leather.  kinda wierd.  After gettin past the aroma the flavor was good. piney, citrusy hops with some malt background.  ill have to revisit this.

From a bottle pours black with small head that faded fast.  aromas of coffee.  More coffee and chocolate notes in the flavor.  A sorta vanilla vodka like taste is in there too which was off putting.  solid stout.

I normally dont go for belguim style beers but maybe Ive been trying the wrong ones because this one was great.  Dark fruit and malty goodness, with an almost wine-like character.   solid mouthfeel with a hint of warming alcohol.  great beer.
Great representation of the IPA style.  citrusy hops, caramel maltyness.  great drinkability.
From a bottle, pours a nice copper color.  Standard ipa taste and aroma.  solid brew non the less.

From a bottle, pours a hazy copper with fluffy white head.  Aroma of pine and some floral hops.  Flavors of more piney hops, caramel and a hint of metal in thefirst few drinks but wentaway .  very bitter, piney ipa.
From a bottle, pours a dark brown.  Dark fruits, caramel, spice and sweet fruit in the nose.  raisins, other dark fruits and spicey hops.  Creamy texture.
Solid IPA.  Pours a nice copper.  Malty caramel with piney, citrusy hops flavors.  Solid IPA.
From a bottle, pours a amber color.  Great hop taste.  Nothing seems out of place in this beer, well balanced.  great sessional beer.
From a bottle pours a dark red/copper color.  Aromas of roasty malts, coffee, and some hops.  big malt taste with some hops in the back.  Creamy body. good brew from Victory.
From a bottle, pours colden color.  Aromas of faint raspberry and wheat.  taste like the aroma.   definetely not on of STs best

From a bottle, pours golden copper color.  Aromas of hops, yeast and a fruityness.  Not much similiarity to other tripels ive had.  didnt notice the alcohol at all, and was actually surprised it was 9%.   Very drinkable.
From a bottle, pours clear copper.  Hints of piney hops, and caramel in the aroma.  Same Flavors as the aroma.  Decent pale ale.
beer_name: Southern Tier PMX (Phin & Matts Extraordinary Ale)

review_blob: From a bottle, pours copper.  Citrusy, piney hops with some floral notes.  Very tasty.
From a bottle, pours a hazy copper with little to no head.  Aromas of tart lemon and some peachy notes.  Taste tart and sweet very wine-like.  Definetely worth a try.

beer_brewer_name: Schneider Weisse G. Schneider & Sohn GmbH
review_blob: from bottle pours a deep amber color.  Dark fruit, yeast, and a wine like aroma.  Notes of more dark fruit, wheat, raisens, and caramel.  creamy texture.  good brew
From a bomber. pours a brownish copper color.  caramel, tea, and toffee in the aroma.  More dark malt, toffee, tea, and some hops in the taste.  Alcohol starts to show in the finish.

From a bottle.  Pours a clear coper color.  Notes of dark fruit and slight hops.  Flavor of a wine like grape flavor, honey and some alcohol burn.  Something wasnt meching with me in this brew, ive had better brews from DFH.
beer_name: Dogfish Head Midas Touch Golden Elixir

review_blob: From a bottle.pours very clear yellow.  very average brew.  Notes of wheat, spice and yeast in the taste and not much else.
From a bottle.  Pours a copper color.  big fruity, citrusy notes in the aroma.  Sweet, citrusy hops in the taste.  this beer is definetely more on the sweeter side of IIPAs.  great brew

On tap.  pours a hazy copper with small white head.  Aromas of piney hops and floral hops.  first sip is a hop punch in the mouth.  very sticky piney taste, with notes of citrus and caramel.  Awsome brew for any hop head.
beer_name: Moylans Hopsickle Imperial India Pale Ale

review_blob: From a bottle. Pours dark copper with off white head.  Oak aging added a little oak flavor to the brew but not anything remarkable.  This is still a great brew but I dont think oak aging was needed to make this brew any better than it is regularly.
